,"status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."},{"name":"Unnamed Security Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Eros Emergency","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A security officer dressed in fake police uniform, part of a corrupt group controlling the crowd.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Recognized from previous arrest"}],"recentEvents":"Observed by Miller as part of the corrupt security force, recognized as previously arrested and wearing stolen equipment."},{"name":"Ko (Unnamed security guard)","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","