ets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A civilian cargo ship.","recentEvents":"The ship was destroyed by a stealth ship using advanced military technology.","relationships":[{"location":"Martian Congressional Republic","relationship":"Was attacked by a ship with technology bearing Martian military serial numbers"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Ceres","arc":"Conflict","description":"A significant asteroid in the solar system that hosts a large mining station and town.","recentEvents":"Captain Shaddid addresses security personnel about an incoming unencrypted message from an unknown source, signaling a potential crisis.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Another major asteroid in the same vicinity"}]},{"name":"Knight","arc":"Investigation","description":"A ship owned by the crew of characters, operating in the asteroid belt.","recentEvents":"The crew of the Knight investigates the distress beacon that turned out to be fake, discovering the derelict Scopuli.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Investigation site for distress signal"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.