atus":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A civilian cargo ship.","recentEvents":"The ship was destroyed by a stealth ship using advanced military technology.","relationships":[{"location":"Martian Congressional Republic","relationship":"Was attacked by a ship with technology bearing Martian military serial numbers"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Ceres","arc":"Mining Colony Conflict","description":"A significant space station and mining hub in the asteroid belt, crucial to the economy and politics of the Belt.","recentEvents":"A mob on Ceres incited to rise against Martian authority resulted in the death of one station worker and serious injury to another, before being dispersed by Detective Miller's intervention.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is in conflict with Mars for independence and equal rights."}]},{"name":"Knight","arc":"Investigation","description":"A ship owned by the crew of characters, operating in the asteroid belt.","recentEvents":"The crew of the Knight investigates the distress beacon that turned out to be fake, discovering the derelict Scopuli.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Investigation site for distress signal"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A battleship of the MCRN Jupiter fleet, known for its formidable capabilities.","recentEvents":"The Canterbury's surviving crew agrees to be picked up by the Donnager while also broadcasting their cooperation to emphasize their safety.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The Knight is instructed to follow a course sent by the Donnager, leading to the confrontation between the two ships."}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Unexplained Disaster on the Scopuli","status":"active","characters":["Julie Mao"],"summary":"Julie discovers the Scopuli in a state of disarray, with signs of a mysterious event that led to the sealing of the engineering hatch, leaving her uncertain about the fate of her shipmates."},{"name":"Space Law and Ethics","status":"active","characters":["Holden","McDowell","Ade","Pilot"],"summary":"The crew is preparing to respond to an emergency signal, weighing the risks and costs of their response against legal and ethical obligations."},{"name":"Ceres Security Dynamics","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Shaddid"],"summary":"Miller is investigating a shift in Ceres's organized crime while also being tasked with finding Julie Mao, a story that seems to be a side mission to the broader investigation of the security dynamics on Ceres."},{"name":"Julie Mao Kidnap","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller has been contracted by Julie Mao’s family to detain her and ship her home, initiating a personal mission that may conflict with his integrity as a detective."},{"name":"Pirate Attack Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Jim and Amos uncover signs of sabotage and deception aboard the Scopuli, leading them to suspect an elaborate trap."},{"name":"Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller's private investigation into tracking down a missing adult daughter proceeds, with potential new developments arising from an urgent network message."},{"name":"Investigation into Canterbury's Destruction","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew decide to cooperate with the MCRN Donnager while broadcasting their actions to undermine potential cover-ups, setting a tense path towards confrontation with the Martian battleship."},{"name":"Detective Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Shirtless","OPA member"],"summary":"Detective Miller successfully de-escalates a violent riot and arrests one of the instigators, emphasizing the danger of internal divisions among Belters."}],"summary":"After the destruction of the Canterbury, its crew is given the ultimatum to either cooperate with the MCRN or face imprisonment. Holden and the crew decide to cooperate cautiously, broadcasting their intent to emphasize their safety while secretly planning resistance against any harmful actions from the MCRN. This confrontation is complicated by the emergence of six unidentified ships also approaching their location."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVe