s and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Space Law and Ethics","status":"active","characters":["Holden","McDowell","Ade","Pilot"],"summary":"The crew is preparing to respond to an emergency signal, weighing the risks and costs of their response against legal and ethical obligations."},{"name":"Ceres Security Dynamics","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Shaddid"],"summary":"Miller is investigating a shift in Ceres's organized crime while also being tasked with finding Julie Mao, a story that seems to be a side mission to the broader investigation of the security dynamics on Ceres."},{"name":"Julie Mao Kidnap","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller has been contracted by Julie Mao’s family to detain her and ship her home, initiating a personal mission that may conflict with his integrity as a detective."},{"name":"Pirate Attack Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Jim and Amos uncover signs of sabotage and deception aboard the Scopuli, leading them to suspect an elaborate trap."},{"name":"Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller's private investigation into tracking down a missing adult daughter proceeds, with potential new developments arising from an urgent network message."},{"name":"Investigation into Canterbury's Destruction","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew decide to cooperate with the MCRN Donnager while broadcasting their actions to undermine potential cover-ups, setting a tense path towards confrontation with the Martian battleship."},{"name":"Detective Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Shirtless","OPA member"],"summary":"Detective Miller successfully de-escalates a violent riot and arrests one of the instigators, emphasizing the danger of internal divisions among Belters."},{"name":"Julie Mao's Disappearance","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Detective Miller has uncovered personal correspondence between Julie Mao and her family, indicating a strained relationship and a critical message from Ariadne Mao regarding the impending danger in the Belt, sent two weeks before the start of the Rifter war."}],"summary":"The story delves into the personal life and background of Julie Mao, a key figure in the Belt's radical OPA movement. Det. Miller investigates her living quarters and digital communications, uncovering family conflicts and hints of political intrigue, while tensions between Mars and the Belt escalate."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":13,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the