's message from the ship's memory."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A veteran detective, Miller is known for his cynicism and a tragic past.","relationships":[{"character":"Vincent Havelock","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Interrogated a bar patron about OPA's influence, visited a bar connected to OPA, learned about Mateo Judd's death."},{"name":"Willis Havelock","aliases":["Havelock","Billy Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Helium-3 security officer, ex-Ombudsman, known for his past as a thief and his relationship with Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, partner"},{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"fellow security officer, overseer"}],"recentEvents":"At the lounge with Miller, engaging in convivial interaction with a vice and exploitation team."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 17: The Butcher","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"The Rocinante's chief engineer and security officer with a dry, acerbic sense of humor.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First officer and strategist"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Voyager"},{"character":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","relationship":"Navigator"}],"recentEvents":"Drank tequila in the galley and expressed frustration about the danger their mission poses."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Josephus Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Earther and Star Helix Security agent, now on a personal mission assigned by Shaddid.","relationships":[{"character":"William Ochoa","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Donna Shader","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent"},{"character":"Chrisjen Avasarala","relationship":"former diplomat"}],"recentEvents":"At the lounge with Havelock and responding to Shaddid's emergency message."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Star Helix Command Center","description":"Captain of Star Helix, Shaddid leads security operations and is a critical figure in Amunet’s corporate hierarchy.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Donna Shader","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"possible investigation target"}],"recentEvents":"Transmitting emergency orders to Star Helix agents regarding an alert from the direction of Saturn."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Shed","Kamal","Alex Kamal"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 17: The Butcher","currentLocation":"Knight","description":"The Rocinante's navigator who is still adjusting to the responsibilities of his new position.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First officer and strategist"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Engineer and security"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Voyager"}],"recentEvents":"Participated in the drinking session in the galley to cope with stress."},{"name":"Shirtless","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A steroid-pumped Belt rioter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered a woman and was incapacitated by Miller."},{"name":"The Woman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A civilian cargo ship.","recentEvents":"The ship was destroyed by a stealth ship using advanced military technology.","relationships":[{"location":"Martian Congressional Republic","relationship":"Was attacked by a ship with technology bearing Martian military serial numbers"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager continues to pursue the Knight, putting pressure on the crew's ability to act freely.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres"],"arc":"The Missing Supply","description":"Space station orbiting planet Ceres, a hub for Belters and a site of recent tensions between Belters and Inner Planets.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's father, JPM, is considering selling the Razorback, a personal boat that has importance to Julie.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Ceres Station's economy is affected by the docking fees charged by Ganymede."},{"location":"Europa","relationship":"Europa contracts were blocked for Belters, impacting Ceres Station economically."},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Ongoing tensions and fear towards Inner Planets like Earth are causing unrest among Belters."},{"location":"Luna","relationship":"Ceres is involved in interplanetary commerce and politics with Luna."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is part of the Belt, in tension with Mars over resources and political power."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Pirate Attack Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Amos Burton"],"summary":"Jim and Amos uncover signs of sabotage and deception aboard the Scopuli, leading them to suspect an elaborate trap."},{"name":"Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller's private investigation into tracking down a missing adult daughter proceeds, with potential new developments arising from an urgent network message."},{"name":"Investigation into Canterbury's Destruction","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew decide to cooperate with the MCRN Donnager while broadcasting their actions to undermine potential cover-ups, setting a tense path towards confrontation with the Martian battleship."},{"name":"Detective Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Shirtless","OPA member"],"summary":"Detective Miller successfully de-escalates a violent riot and arrests one of the instigators, emphasizing the danger of internal divisions among Belters."},{"name":"Julie Mao's Disappearance","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Detective Miller has uncovered personal correspondence between Julie Mao and her family, indicating a strained relationship and a critical message from Ariadne Mao regarding the impending danger in the Belt, sent two weeks before the start of the Rifter war."},{"name":"Navigating Martian Interception","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex","Ships"],"summary":"The crew continues to navigate towards Jupiter, with new mysterious ships pursuing and the Martian Donnager still hot on their trail, compounding their sense of confusion and threat."},{"name":"Colonel Johnson's Invitation","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"Holden receives a private message from Colonel Johnson recommending caution and providing an escape keyword, signaling the start of potential aid and communication with the OPA."},{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller now suspects OPA may be targeting the police force in Ceres, following the assassination of Mateo Judd, who was previously believed to be an OPA member based on his appearance of the symbol."}],"summary":"Miller investigates the OPA's presence on Ceres Station, questioning its involvement in recent crime waves. He encounters resistance and confusion, leading to Mateo Judd's murder and deepening the mystery of Julie Mao's disappearance."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":15,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from her mother warning the Belt is becoming unsafe and urging her to return home."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","re