er":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Aleksandr Mahotina","aliases":["Alex"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"The Rocinante's navigator, known for his technical expertise and calm demeanor.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and friend"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First officer and friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and friend"}],"recentEvents":"Alex was monitoring the sensors during the battle when the Donnager was hit by a torpedo, warning the crew about the upcoming impact."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A civilian cargo ship.","recentEvents":"The ship was destroyed by a stealth ship using advanced military technology.","relationships":[{"location":"Martian Congressional Republic","relationship":"Was attacked by a ship with technology bearing Martian military serial numbers"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres"],"arc":"The Missing Supply","description":"Space station orbiting planet Ceres, a hub for Belters and a site of recent tensions between Belters and Inner Planets.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's father, JPM, is considering selling the Razorback, a personal boat that has importance to Julie.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"Ceres Station's economy is affected by the docking fees charged by Ganymede."},{"location":"Europa","relationship":"Europa contracts were blocked for Belters, impacting Ceres Station economically."},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Ongoing tensions and fear towards Inner Planets like Earth are causing unrest among Belters."},{"location":"Luna","relationship":"Ceres is involved in interplanetary commerce and politics with Luna."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is part of the Belt, in tension with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller's private investigation into tracking down a missing adult daughter proceeds, with potential new developments arising from an urgent network message."},{"name":"Investigation into Canterbury's Destruction","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew decide to cooperate with the MCRN Donnager while broadcasting their actions to undermine potential cover-ups, setting a tense path towards confrontation with the Martian battleship."},{"name":"Detective Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Shirtless","OPA member"],"summary":"Detective Miller successfully de-escalates a violent riot and arrests one of the instigators, emphasizing the danger of internal divisions among Belters."},{"name":"Julie Mao's Disappearance","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Detective Miller has uncovered personal correspondence between Julie Mao and her family, indicating a strained relationship and a critical message from Ariadne Mao regarding the impending danger in the Belt, sent two weeks before the start of the Rifter war."},{"name":"Navigating Martian Interception","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex","Ships"],"summary":"The crew continues to navigate towards Jupiter, with new mysterious ships pursuing and the Martian Donnager still hot on their trail, compounding their sense of confusion and threat."},{"name":"Colonel Johnson's Invitation","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"Holden receives a private message from Colonel Johnson recommending caution and providing an escape keyword, signaling the start of potential aid and communication with the OPA."},{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller now suspects OPA may be targeting the police force in Ceres, following the assassination of Mateo Judd, who was previously believed to be an OPA member based on his appearance of the symbol."},{"name":"The Return to Donnager","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The crew finds themselves caught in the middle of a desperate close-quarters battle as Donnager is hit by a torpedo, and Shed is killed by gauss turret fire."}],"summary":"The crew of the spacecraft Donnager is locked in a desperate battle against a mysterious fleet, with the ship's systems activating to fend off incoming attacks. Amidst the chaos, one crew member is killed by a rogue gauss round, and the crew struggles to understand the unfolding events."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":16,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from her mother warning the Belt is becoming unsafe and urging her to return home."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain of Julie's ship"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captain Darren's head appears fused to the reactor in an unknown form, asking for help, suggesting he is among those in the engineering deck."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Mike was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Wan Li was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"William Orlowski","aliases":["Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"The captain of the Rocinante, a former United Nations Marine Corps officer known for his leadership and moral integrity.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer and close friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and close friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Holden was questioned by a naval intelligence officer on the Donnager and later became aware of a torpedo attack on the Donnager, leading to the death of a crew member (Shed). The ship has become a battlefield due to a close-quarters battle."},{"name":"Ava Tukunbo","aliases":["Ava","Navigator"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A skilled navigator with a talent for quick thinking and a warm voice.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ava calculated that the Canterbury could reach the emergency signal's location within two days, despite being fully loaded with ice."},{"name":"Mark Paj","aliases":["Paj","Engineer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A resourceful engineer with a tough exterior and a habit of getting into dangerous situations.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"}],"recentEvents":"Mark had his arm injured while shifting ice, and the ship needed to respond to an emergency signal despite being fully loaded."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi","First Officer","Nomi","Navcom","Navigation & Communication"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"A former operative for the Martian government who is now the first mate and doctor on the Rocinante.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and close friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Naomi was questioned by a naval intelligence officer on the Donnager and became concerned about the actions of the Belt ships, which have now resulted in a torpedo hitting the Donnager."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A veteran detective, Miller is known for his cynicism and a tragic past.","relationships":[{"character":"Vincent Havelock","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Interrogated a bar patron about OPA's influence, visited a bar connected to OPA, learned about Mateo Judd's death."},{"name":"Willis Havelock","aliases":["Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"Miller's closest friend and colleague on Eros Station, likely another security officer for Mars Industries with knowledge of Eros' secrets.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Miller called Havelock to take leave and evacuate the station as tensions rise due to OPA's fears of a potential war."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down"],"importance":"m