 of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An agent of the Outer Planets Alliance (OPA), who visits Eros Station with concerns regarding Josephus Miller's investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to convince Miller to abandon his search for Julie Mao, indicating Dawes' awareness of a growing crisis situation."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A civilian cargo ship.","recentEvents":"The ship was destroyed by a stealth ship using advanced military technology.","relationships":[{"location":"Martian Congressional Republic","relationship":"Was attacked by a ship with technology bearing Martian military serial numbers"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres"],"arc":"Power Struggle","description":"A station located in the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter, serving as a hub for mining operations and a symbol of autonomy for Belters.","recentEvents":"An OPA agent visits Detective Miller, warning him about potential risks involved with his investigation and suggesting that the OPA is apprehensive.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Part of the asteroid belt, relevant in the context of interstellar navigation and conflict."}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros","arc":"Power Struggle","description":"A station in the asteroid belt, part of the setting where mining activities and social tensions among Belters play out.","recentEvents":"Miller is advised to take precautions and leave the station, suggesting heightened tensions and potential threats.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of the same asteroid belt, interconnected in terms of mining operations and political issues."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Investigation into Canterbury's Destruction","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"Holden and his crew decide to cooperate with the MCRN Donnager while broadcasting their actions to undermine potential cover-ups, setting a tense path towards confrontation with the Martian battleship."},{"name":"Detective Miller's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Shirtless","OPA member"],"summary":"Detective Miller successfully de-escalates a violent riot and arrests one of the instigators, emphasizing the danger of internal divisions among Belters."},{"name":"Julie Mao's Disappearance","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Detective Miller has uncovered personal correspondence between Julie Mao and her family, indicating a strained relationship and a critical message from Ariadne Mao regarding the impending danger in the Belt, sent two weeks before the start of the Rifter war."},{"name":"Navigating Martian Interception","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex","Ships"],"summary":"The crew continues to navigate towards Jupiter, with new mysterious ships pursuing and the Martian Donnager still hot on their trail, compounding their sense of confusion and threat."},{"name":"Colonel Johnson's Invitation","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"Holden receives a private message from Colonel Johnson recommending caution and providing an escape keyword, signaling the start of potential aid and communication with the OPA."},{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller now suspects OPA may be targeting the police force in Ceres, following the assassination of Mateo Judd, who was previously believed to be an OPA member based on his appearance of the symbol."},{"name":"The Return to Donnager","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The crew finds themselves caught in the middle of a desperate close-quarters battle as Donnager is hit by a torpedo, and Shed is killed by gauss turret fire."},{"name":"Search for Julie","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller learns Julie was on the Scopuli, the freighter used as bait by Mars to kill the Canterbury. He warns Havelock to take leave and go somewhere safe due to potential dangers."}],"summary":"Detective Miller receives a visit from an OPA agent who warns him about potential risks related to his investigation of Julie's kidnapping and suggests taking a leave of absence. Miller suspects that the OPA is worried about growing instability and conflicts, leading him to advise his partner Havelock to take protective measures."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":17,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from her mother warning the Belt is becoming unsafe and urging her to return home."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain of Julie's ship"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captain Darren's head appears fused to the reactor in an unknown form, asking for help, suggesting he is among those in the engineering deck."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Mike was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Wan Li was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"William Orlowski","aliases":["Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"The captain of the Rocinante, a former United Nations Marine Corps officer known for his leadership and moral integrity.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer and close friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and close friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Holden was questioned by a naval intelligence officer on the Donnager and later became aware of a torpedo attack on the Donnager, leading to the death of a crew member (Shed). The ship has become a battlefield due to a close-quarters battle."},{"name":"Ava Tukunbo","aliases":["Ava","Navigator"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A skilled navigator with a talent for quick thinking and a warm voice.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ava calculated that the Canterbury could reach the emergency signal's location within two days, despite being fully loaded with ice."},{"name":"Mark Paj","aliases":["Paj","Engineer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A resourceful engineer with a tough exterior and a habit of getting into dangerous situations.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"}],"recentEvents":"Mark had his arm injured while shifting ice, and the ship needed to respond to an emergency signal despite being fully loaded."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi","First Officer","Nomi","Navcom","Navigation & Communication"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"A former operative for the Martian government who is now the first mate and doctor on the Rocinante.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and close friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Naomi was questioned by a naval intelligence officer on the Donnager and became concerned about the actions of the Belt ships, which have now resulted in a torpedo hitting the Donnager."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A veteran detective, Miller is known for his cynicism and a tragic past.","relationships":[{"character":"Vincent Havelock","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Interrogated a bar patron about OPA's influence, visited a bar connected to OPA, learned about Mateo Judd's death."},{"name":"Willis Havelock","aliases":["Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"Miller's closest friend and colleague on Eros Station, likely another security officer for Mars Industries with knowledge of Eros' secrets.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Miller called Havelock to take leave and evacuate the station as tensions rise due to OPA's fears of a potential war."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"The Rocinante's chief engineer, known for his blunt honesty and loyalty.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and close friend"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First officer and friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Amos was questioning the sanity of the situation as a torpedo hit the Donnager, causing the ship to lose gravity and creating fear among the crew."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Josephus Miller","aliases":["Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A hardened detective and security officer with Mars Industries, living on Eros Station, former military service and now working for Earther corporations among Belters.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Wayne Havelock","relationship":"Collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Received a visit from an OPA agent who attempted to dissuade Miller from searching for Julie Mao; Miller suspects the agent's fear indicates growing instability on Eros Station."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Star Helix Command Center","description":"Captain of Star Helix, Shaddid leads security operations and is a critical figure in Amunet’s corporate hierarchy.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Donna Shader","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"possible investigation target"}],"recentEvents":"Transmitting emergency orders to Star Helix agents regarding an alert from the direction of Saturn."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Shed","Kamal","Alex Kamal"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"A medic on the Ro