with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A space station in the Asteroid Belt, crucial for trade and resource extraction, and a strategic target due to its size and resources.","recentEvents":"Detective Miller investigates a police equipment theft, implicating local organized crime and off-station transfers. He also meets with Anderson Dawes from the Outer Planets Alliance.","relationships":[{"location":"Ganymede","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and possibly personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros","arc":"Power Struggle","description":"A station in the asteroid belt, part of the setting where mining activities and social tensions among Belters play out.","recentEvents":"Miller is advised to take precautions and leave the station, suggesting heightened tensions and potential threats.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of the same asteroid belt, interconnected in terms of mining operations and political issues."}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","arc":"Conflict","description":"A large moon of Jupiter, significant for its role in interplanetary trade and being a staging point for operations involving Ceres.","recentEvents":"Serves as the destination for the Black Cat freighter carrying stolen police equipment from Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Julie Mao's Disappearance","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie Mao"],"summary":"Detective Miller has uncovered personal correspondence between Julie Mao and her family, indicating a strained relationship and a critical message from Ariadne Mao regarding the impending danger in the Belt, sent two weeks before the start of the Rifter war."},{"name":"Navigating Martian Interception","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex","Ships"],"summary":"The crew continues to navigate towards Jupiter, with new mysterious ships pursuing and the Martian Donnager still hot on their trail, compounding their sense of confusion and threat."},{"name":"Colonel Johnson's Invitation","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"Holden receives a private message from Colonel Johnson recommending caution and providing an escape keyword, signaling the start of potential aid and communication with the OPA."},{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller now suspects OPA may be targeting the police force in Ceres, following the assassination of Mateo Judd, who was previously believed to be an OPA member based on his appearance of the symbol."},{"name":"The Return to Donnager","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The crew finds themselves caught in the middle of a desperate close-quarters battle as Donnager is hit by a torpedo, and Shed is killed by gauss turret fire."},{"name":"Search for Julie","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller learns Julie was on the Scopuli, the freighter used as bait by Mars to kill the Canterbury. He warns Havelock to take leave and go somewhere safe due to potential dangers."},{"name":"The Canterbury's Wreckage","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Amos","Alex","Naomi","Kelly","Gomez","Dookie"],"summary":"The crew narrowly escapes an enemy boarding party in the aftermath of the Canterbury's destruction, facing a new threat within the hangar bay."},{"name":"Detective Miller's OPA Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"Detective Miller has agreed to drop the Mao investigation but retains some level of commitment or interest in finding her through his agreement with Anderson Dawes."}],"summary":"Detective Miller investigates a minor case of police equipment theft on Ceres, uncovering a trail leading to organized crime and off-station transfers, while privately pursuing the OPA's Juliette Mao's whereabouts, eventually negotiating a deal with Dawes."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":19,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from her mother warning the Belt is becoming unsafe and urging her to return home."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain of Julie's ship"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captain Darren's head appears fused to the reactor in an unknown form, asking for help, suggesting he is among those in the engineering deck."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Mike was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Wan Li was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"William Orlowski","aliases":["Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Torpedo Bomber","description":"The captain of the Rocinante, a former MCRN officer, and a key leader in events around the protomolecule and anti-MCRN organization OPA.","relationships":[{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Second-in-command officer and friend"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Helmsman and fellow MCRN veteran"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Leader of the OPA and key ally"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from Fred Johnson offering help and instructions. Turned off the transponder and communicated with Johnson in a secure manner. Planning to head to a secret OPA location."},{"name":"Ava Tukunbo","aliases":["Ava","Navigator"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A skilled navigator with a talent for quick thinking and a warm voice.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer"}],"recentEvents":"Ava calculated that the Canterbury could reach the emergency signal's location within two days, despite being fully loaded with ice."},{"name":"Mark Paj","aliases":["Paj","Engineer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A resourceful engineer with a tough exterior and a habit of getting into dangerous situations.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"}],"recentEvents":"Mark had his arm injured while shifting ice, and the ship needed to respond to an emergency signal despite being fully loaded."},{"name":"Fred Johnson","aliases":["Naomi","First Officer","Nomi","Navcom","Navigation & Communication","no alias","Naomi Nagata"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The charismatic leader of the Outer Planets Alliance (OPA) and an anti-Earth and anti-Mars political figure. His organization works against the Earth-Mars Coalition.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Key ally and supporter"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Allied colleague"},{"character":"Alexander Kamal","relationship":"Allied colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to James Holden providing a new transponder code and safe location coordinates enabling the MCRN gunboat to evade detection while navigating to an OPA-controlled space station or planet."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller","the cop","Miller","Josephus Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A hardened detective and security officer with Mars Industries, living on Eros Station, former military service and now working for Earther corporations among Belters.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Client"},{"character":"Wayne Havelock","relationship":"Collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Received a visit from an OPA agent who attempted to dissuade Miller from searching for Julie Mao; Miller suspects the agent's fear indicates growing instability on Eros Station."},{"name":"Willis Havelock","aliases":["Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"Miller's closest friend and colleague on Eros Station, likely another security officer for Mars Industries with knowledge of Eros' secrets.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Miller called Havelock to take leave and evacuate the station as tensions rise due to OPA's fears of a potential war."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"The Rocinante's chief engineer, known for his blunt honesty and loyalty.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and close friend"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First officer and friend"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and friend, also known as Alex"}],"recentEvents":"Amos was questioning the sanity of the situation as a torpedo hit the Donnager, causing the ship to lose gravity and creating fear among the crew."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Star Helix Command Center","description":"Captain of Star Helix, Shaddid leads security operations and is a critical figure in Amunet’s corporate hierarchy.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Donna Shader","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"possible investigation target"}],"recentEvents":"Transmitting emergency orders to Star Helix agents regarding an alert from the direction of Saturn."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Shed","Kamal","Alex Kamal"],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"A medic on the Rocinante.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"First Officer and crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer and crew member"},{"character":"Aleksandr Mahotina","relationship":"Navigator and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Shed was killed when a Gauss round hit the Rocinante, shearing off his upper body."},{"name":"Shirtless","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A steroid-pumped Belt rioter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered a woman and was incapacitated by Miller."},{"name":"The Woman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Aleksandr Mahotina","aliases":["Alex","Alexander Kamal"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Torpedo Bomber","description":"Former MCRN pilot, the helmsman of the Rocinante, and a close friend to the crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and superior"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crewmate and friend"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Allied leader through OPA"}],"recentEvents":"Turned off the transponder signal of the MCRN gunboat to evade detection. Set a course to the coordinates given to Holden by Fred Johnson."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An agent of the Outer Planets Alliance (OPA), who visits Eros Station with concerns regarding Josephus Miller's investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to convince Miller to abandon his search for Julie Mao, indicating Dawes' awareness of a growing crisis situation."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["none"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Butcher of Anderson Station","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A member of the Outer Planets Alliance, Dawes is also Miller's informant.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"informant and occasional aide"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with information on the police equipment raid and confirmed the involvement of the Black Cat organization."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association w