es."}]},{"name":"Tachi","arc":"The Donnager Event","description":"A salvaged MCRN gunboat now in Jim Holden's possession.","recentEvents":"Jim Holden and his crew use Tachi to escape the battle and seek refuge from the MCRN.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN","relationship":"Currently evading"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller now suspects OPA may be targeting the police force in Ceres, following the assassination of Mateo Judd, who was previously believed to be an OPA member based on his appearance of the symbol."},{"name":"The Return to Donnager","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Amos Burton","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The crew finds themselves caught in the middle of a desperate close-quarters battle as Donnager is hit by a torpedo, and Shed is killed by gauss turret fire."},{"name":"Search for Julie","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Havelock"],"summary":"Miller learns Julie was on the Scopuli, the freighter used as bait by Mars to kill the Canterbury. He warns Havelock to take leave and go somewhere safe due to potential dangers."},{"name":"The Canterbury's Wreckage","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Amos","Alex","Naomi","Kelly","Gomez","Dookie"],"summary":"The crew narrowly escapes an enemy boarding party in the aftermath of the Canterbury's destruction, facing a new threat within the hangar bay."},{"name":"Detective Miller's OPA Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Detective Miller","Anderson Dawes"],"summary":"Detective Miller has agreed to drop the Mao investigation but retains some level of commitment or interest in finding her through his agreement with Anderson Dawes."},{"name":"Surviving the Donnager incident","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The team has escaped the Donnager and is now seeking assistance from Fred Johnson, potentially revealing a new level of OPA capa