:"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: Departure","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Former security head of Anderson Station and a key mentor for Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Friend, mentor"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Welcomed the crew of the Rocinante to Tycho Station and greeted them upon arrival."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Detective Miller","aliases":["Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller","the cop","Miller","Josephus Miller","Cop","James Miller"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Wrong Road","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"A fifty-year-old former special agent and current police officer, known for his dedication and past reputation as a skilled detective.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Romantic interest"},{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Struggled with drinking and personal issues after Julie Mao was taken away from him by higher-ups."},{"name":"Willis Havelock","aliases":["Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"Miller's closest friend and colleague on Eros Station, likely another security officer for Mars Industries with knowledge of Eros' secrets.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Miller called Havelock to take leave and evacuate the station as tensions rise due to OPA's fears of a potential war."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down","Amo","A.B."],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: Departure","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Engineer and mechanic for the crew of the Rocinante, known for his no-nonsense attitude and military background.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Friend, captain"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friend, crew member"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Friend, crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Friend, mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Visited Tycho Station with the crew to pick up new weapons. Stated his approval of Holden's decision to be armed."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Star Helix Command Center","description":"Captain of Star Helix, Shaddid leads security operations and is a critical figure in Amunet’s corporate hierarchy.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Donna Shader","relationship":"agent, under her command"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"possible investigation target"}],"recentEvents":"Transmitting emergency orders to Star Helix agents regarding an alert from the direction of Saturn."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Shed","Kamal","Alex Kamal","Astro"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 1: Departure","currentLocation":"Tycho Station","description":"Pilot of the Rocinante, known for his laid-back personality and expertise in flying.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Friend, captain"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Friend, crew member"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Friend, crew member"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Friend, mentor"}],"recentEvents":"Visited Tycho Station with the crew to pick up new weapons. Guided the Rocinante into Tycho Station's docking port."},{"name":"Shirtless","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A steroid-pumped Belt rioter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered a woman and was incapacitated by Miller."},{"name":"The Woman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Aleksandr Mahotina","aliases":["Alex","Alexander Kamal"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Torpedo Bomber","description":"Former MCRN pilot, the helmsman of the Rocinante, and a close friend to the crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and superior"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crewmate and friend"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Allied leader through OPA"}],"recentEvents":"Turned off the transponder signal of the MCRN gunboat to evade detection. Set a course to the coordinates given to Holden by Fred Johnson."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Nemesis","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"An agent of the Outer Planets Alliance (OPA), who visits Eros Station with concerns regarding Josephus Miller's investigation.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"Attempted to convince Miller to abandon his search for Julie Mao, indicating Dawes' awareness of a growing crisis situation."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["none"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Butcher of Anderson Station","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A member of the Outer Planets Alliance, Dawes is also Miller's informant.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"informant and occasional aide"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with information on the police equipment raid and confirmed the involvement of the Black Cat organization."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Krista Muss","aliases":["Muss"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Wrong Road","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Miller's new policing partner, initially seen as a joke assignment but who shows understanding and patience.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Policing partner"}],"recentEvents":"Worked with Miller on regular policing duties, showing compassion towards his struggle with the Julie Mao case."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"War Declarations and Inquiries","description":"A dwarf planet and major settlement in the asteroid belt, host to the station house and daily life events of former detective Miller.","recentEvents":"Miller had a difficult 