 finding her through his agreement with Anderson Dawes."},{"name":"Surviving the Donnager incident","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata","Alex Kamal"],"summary":"The team has escaped the Donnager and is now seeking assistance from Fred Johnson, potentially revealing a new level of OPA capabilities."},{"name":"Finding Julie","status":"active","characters":["Josephus Miller"],"summary":"Miller is frustrated with the loss of his case on Julie, recognizing it as a special and personal matter rather than just a professional case."},{"name":"Miller's Professional Decline","status":"active","characters":["Josephus Miller","Muss"],"summary":"Miller experiences a personal low, feeling that his career is at a downturn and that he's been assigned challenging cases as a form of punishment or due to perceived underperformance."},{"name":"Rocinante's Redemption","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Amos","Naomi","Alex"],"summary":"The crew of the newly christened Rocinante prepares to seek their future under Fred's guidance at Tycho Station."}],"summary":"Holden acquires a new ship, the Rocinante, and heads to Tycho Station for repairs and upgrades. Upon arrival, they are greeted by Fred, the Butcher of Anderson Station, marking a shift in the crew's stance towards confrontation with authority figures."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":22,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The estranged daughter of wealthy CEO Jules-Pierre Mao, she values freedom and lives independently in the Belt.","relationships":[{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Mother"}],"recentEvents":"Received a message from her mother warning the Belt is becoming unsafe and urging her to return home."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"im