ion":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Aleksandr Mahotina","aliases":["Alex","Alexander Kamal"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Torpedo Bomber","description":"Former MCRN pilot, the helmsman of the Rocinante, and a close friend to the crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and superior"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crewmate and friend"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Allied leader through OPA"}],"recentEvents":"Turned off the transponder signal of the MCRN gunboat to evade detection. Set a course to the coordinates given to Holden by Fred Johnson."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Anderson Dawes","aliases":["none"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Butcher of Anderson Station","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A member of the Outer Planets Alliance, Dawes is also Miller's informant.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"informant and occasional aide"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with information on the police equipment raid and confirmed the involvement of the Black Cat organization."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A space station in the asteroid belt populated by miners and settlers","recentEvents":"Ceres experienced several riots and a curfew was imposed to maintain stability amid growing tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is caught in the conflict between Mars and Earth"},{"location":"Tycho","relationship":"Ceres residents begin to seek refuge on Tycho"}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros Station","aliases":["the playhouse","Eros"],"arc":"Drowning Deep","description":"A space station located in the Eros asteroid in the Eros system, a popular destination for its casinos and other entertainment venues.","recentEvents":"Miller finds Juliette Andromeda Mao dead in a hotel room, having undergone a horrific transformation.","relationships":[{"location":"United Nations Security Office","relationship":"Connected via communication and transport links"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","arc":"Conflict","description":"A large moon of Jupiter, significant for its role in interplanetary trade and being a staging point for operations involving Ceres.","recentEvents":"Serves as the destination for the Black Cat freighter carrying stolen police equipment from Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]},{"name":"Tachi","arc":"The Donnager Event","description":"A salvaged MCRN gunboat now in Jim Holden's possession.","recentEvents":"Jim Holden and his crew use Tachi to escape the battle and seek refuge from the MCRN.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN","relationship":"Currently evading"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho Manufacturing and Engineering Concern"],"arc":"The Expansion","description":"A large orbital station circling a planet, serving as a hub for space travel and commerce.","recentEvents":"The crew is spending time on Tycho to rest and gather information before deciding their next steps.","relationships":[{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The crew visits and repairs the ship docked at Tycho"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"The Expansion","description":"The ship the crew is using for their missions, a modified old transport.","recentEvents":"Holden comforts himself by spending time in the cockpit, connecting with the silent ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Docked at Tycho Station"}]},{"name":"Triton","arc":"Conflict","description":"A moon of Neptune with a deep astronomy lab occupied by OPA supporters","recentEvents":"Triton's astronomy lab was taken over and used to broadcast sensitive information about Mars, escalating tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Broadcasting details of Mars' military positions and activities"},{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Increased unrest on Ceres due to Triton's actions"}]},{"name":"Triton Astronomy Lab","arc":"Conflict","description":"A facility on Triton taken over by a band of OPA supporters for broadcasting","recentEvents":"Used to broadcast the locations of all Martian ships and high-definition images of Mars, causing further tension.","relationships":[{"location":"Triton","relationship":"Contained within Triton and a hot spot of conflict"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Causing significant information leaks about Mars' military positions"}]},{"name":"Tycho","arc":"Tycho","description":"A large facility established on the Moon's surface.","recentEvents":"Holden negotiates with Fred Johnson to work for him and is tasked with retrieving a man named Lionel Polanski from Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Eros is one of the many orbital stations serving the Tycho facility as part of Fred Johnson's operations"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Astronaut Detective's Investigation","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller's investigation into Julie's involvement with OPA activities continues as he processes the political changes on Ceres."},{"name":"Ceres Law Enforcement","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Muss"],"summary":"Miller is fired from his position and must navigate the new political landscape on Ceres while Muss is involved in 'cleanup' activities."},{"name":"Tracking Julie Mao","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller is now heading to Eros to find James Holden after receiving information from Lieutenant Havelock about Julie Mao's possible whereabouts."},{"name":"Captain Holden's Mission","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Amos","Naomi"],"summary":"Holden has agreed to help Fred by taking on a covert mission to Eros involving a false identity and a mysterious ship owner named Lionel Polanski."},{"name":"Investigating Julie's Case","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller is now on Eros, waiting for the Rocinante's crew to arrive so he can move forward with his investigation."},{"name":"Political Tensions in the Belt","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Sematimba"],"summary":"With the change in contract management at Eros, political tensions are high and new conflicts arise, impacting Miller's ability to conduct his investigation."},{"name":"Cops Will Be Here Soon","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller meet in the midst of a gunfight, with Miller saving Holden's team from flankers."},{"name":"RenamedArcs[\"Arc Continues\" to \"Arc Converges\"]","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex","Naomi","Amos"],"summary":"The team, led by Holden, finds themselves in a dangerous confrontation with armed individuals in a flophouse, with the involvement of Miller adding a new dynamic."}],"summary":"Detective Miller discovers Juliette Andromeda Mao's mutilated body in a hotel room on Eros Station, indicating a connection to a larger conspiracy involving James Holden, who is believed to be dead. Miller warns Eros security chief Sematimba about the depth of the conspiracy and the danger involved."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":29,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback","N/A","Muss","Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss","Captain Holden","William Orlowski","Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock","Candace","Willis Havelock","Detective Muss","Krista Muss","Miller","Joseph Michael Miller","Julie","Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller","the cop","Josephus Miller","Cop","James Miller","Joseph","old man","cerebral cop","cop","peace officer","Detective Miller","The man with the hat","Joseph Sematimba","partner","Juliette Mao","Cap&#39;n"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 3","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"Detective helping the crew find a missing person.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Collaborator"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Collaborator"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Collaborator"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Collaborator"}],"recentEvents":"Identified the possible origin of the Phoebe bug and suggested his involvement in investigating the asteroid BA834024112."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain of Julie's ship"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captain Darren's head appears fused to the reactor in an unknown form, asking for help, suggesting he is among those in the engineering deck."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Mike was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Wan Li was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Ava","Navigator","Pilot","Alex Kamal","Shed","Kamal","Astro","Ava Tukunbo"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chap