]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A space station in the asteroid belt populated by miners and settlers","recentEvents":"Ceres experienced several riots and a curfew was imposed to maintain stability amid growing tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is caught in the conflict between Mars and Earth"},{"location":"Tycho","relationship":"Ceres residents begin to seek refuge on Tycho"}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros Station","aliases":["the playhouse","Eros","asteroid"],"arc":"the Protogen project","description":"An asteroid where a Protogen project has taken place, leading to mysterious evacuations and possible alien influence.","recentEvents":"Miller and Holden investigate evacuation details, leading to conflicts with security forces and discoveries involving Protogen's activities.","relationships":[{"location":"the hideout","relationship":"a secret location within Eros where the crew had been hiding"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","arc":"Conflict","description":"A large moon of Jupiter, significant for its role in interplanetary trade and being a staging point for operations involving Ceres.","recentEvents":"Serves as the destination for the Black Cat freighter carrying stolen police equipment from Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]},{"name":"Tachi","arc":"The Donnager Event","description":"A salvaged MCRN gunboat now in Jim Holden's possession.","recentEvents":"Jim Holden and his crew use Tachi to escape the battle and seek refuge from the MCRN.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN","relationship":"Currently evading"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho Manufacturing and Engineering Concern"],"arc":"The Expansion","description":"A large orbital station circling a planet, serving as a hub for space travel and commerce.","recentEvents":"The crew is spending time on Tycho to rest and gather information before deciding their next steps.","relationships":[{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The crew visits and repairs the ship docked at Tycho"}]},{"name":"Rocinante","aliases":["Roci"],"arc":"The Expansion","description":"The ship the crew is using for their missions, a modified old transport.","recentEvents":"Holden comforts himself by spending time in the cockpit, connecting with the silent ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Tycho Station","relationship":"Docked at Tycho Station"}]},{"name":"Triton","arc":"Conflict","description":"A moon of Neptune with a deep astronomy lab occupied by OPA supporters","recentEvents":"Triton's astronomy lab was taken over and used to broadcast sensitive information about Mars, escalating tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Broadcasting details of Mars' military positions and activities"},{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Increased unrest on Ceres due to Triton's actions"}]},{"name":"Triton Astronomy Lab","arc":"Conflict","description":"A facility on Triton taken over by a band of OPA supporters for broadcasting","recentEvents":"Used to broadcast the locations of all Martian ships and high-definition images of Mars, causing further tension.","relationships":[{"location":"Triton","relationship":"Contained within Triton and a hot spot of conflict"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Causing significant information leaks about Mars' military positions"}]},{"name":"Tycho","arc":"Tycho","description":"A large facility established on the Moon's surface.","recentEvents":"Holden negotiates with Fred Johnson to work for him and is tasked with retrieving a man named Lionel Polanski from Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Eros is one of the many orbital stations serving the Tycho facility as part of Fred Johnson's operations"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Political Tensions in the Belt","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Sematimba"],"summary":"With the change in contract management at Eros, political tensions are high and new conflicts arise, impacting Miller's ability to conduct his investigation."},{"name":"Cops Will Be Here Soon","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller meet in the midst of a gunfight, with Miller saving Holden's team from flankers."},{"name":"RenamedArcs[\"Arc Continues\" to \"Arc Converges\"]","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Alex","Naomi","Amos"],"summary":"The team, led by Holden, finds themselves in a dangerous confrontation with armed individuals in a flophouse, with the involvement of Miller adding a new dynamic."},{"name":"Search for the Missing - Jim and Miller’s Personal Motivation","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Josephus Miller"],"summary":"Jim and Miller's personal quest remains central, with Miller now driven by a desire for justice for the infected crewmember he sought after."},{"name":"The Phoebe Incident - The Infection's Origin","status":"active","characters":["Jim Holden","Naomi Nagata"],"summary":"The Phoebe Incident and its deadly infection are identified as a potential key to understanding the broader conspiracy."},{"name":"The Canterbury Disaster","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden","Amos","Naomi"],"summary":"Miller uncovers that the security personnel on Eros are part of a prolonged, coordinated effort using stolen Ceres Station equipment, indicating a much larger and more complex conspiracy."},{"name":"Radiation Shelter Discoveries","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller discover that the radiation shelters are laced with gas and radiation, leading to the conclusion that the population may have been infected or poisoned."},{"name":"Investigating Eros's Evacuation","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Josephus Miller"],"summary":"Miller and Holden successfully navigate through Eros to their hideout but discover that Naomi, Alex, and Amos are missing."}],"summary":"Miller and Holden navigate Eros investigating the evacuation details, encountering security forces and facing moral dilemmas involving violence and loss of humanity. They return to their abandoned hideout, finding it empty as their timeline tightens."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":33,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback","N/A","Muss","Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss","Captain Holden","William Orlowski","Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock","Candace","Willis Havelock","Detective Muss","Krista Muss","Miller","Joseph Michael Miller","Julie","Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller","the cop","Josephus Miller","Cop","James Miller","Joseph","old man","cerebral cop","cop","peace officer","Detective Miller","The man with the hat","Joseph Sematimba","partner","Juliette Mao","Cap&#39;n","none","Anderson Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Butcher of Anderson Station","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A member of the Outer Planets Alliance, Dawes is also Miller's informant.","relationships":[{"character":"Miller","relationship":"informant and occasional aide"}],"recentEvents":"Provided Miller with information on the police equipment raid and confirmed the involvement of the Black Cat organization."},{"name":"Dave","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mechanic of Julie's ship; she describes him as someone who collects clips from old cartoons and knows a million jokes.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Dave was heard to be in distress in an apparent torture situation, begging in a small broken voice."},{"name":"Captain Darren","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The captain of the Scopuli, who rolled over like a dog when the kidnappers arrived.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Captain of Julie's ship"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate and mechanic"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Captain Darren's head appears fused to the reactor in an unknown form, asking for help, suggesting he is among those in the engineering deck."},{"name":"Mike","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Wan Li","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Mike was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Wan Li","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"uncertain","lastSeen":"Prologue: Julie","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A shipmate of Julie's; no additional information provided in the text.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Dave","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Captain Darren","relationship":"Shipmate"},{"character":"Mike","relationship":"Shipmate"}],"recentEvents":"Wan Li was one of the shipmates who was taken by the kidnappers, but no specific events are detailed for him."},{"name":"Shawn \"Shed\" Desjardin","aliases":["Ava","Navigator","Pilot","Alex Kamal","Shed","Kamal","Astro","Ava Tukunbo","Alex","Navigation Officer","Alexander Kamal","Aleksandr Mahotina"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Return Only Changes","currentLocation":"Torpedo Bomber","description":"Former MCRN pilot, the helmsman of the Rocinante, and a close friend to the crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and superior"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crewmate and friend"},{"character":"Fred Johnson","relationship":"Allied leader through OPA"}],"recentEvents":"Turned off the transponder signal of the MCRN gunboat to evade detection. Set a course to the coordinates given to Holden by Fred Johnson."},{"name":"Mark Paj","aliases":["Paj","Engineer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"A resourceful engineer with a tough exterior and a habit of getting into dangerous situations.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Captain"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Chief Engineer"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"}],"recentEvents":"Mark had his arm injured while shifting ice, and the ship needed to respond to an emergency signal despite being fully loaded."},{"name":"Naomi Nagata","aliases":["Naomi","First Officer","Nomi","Navcom","Navigation & Communication","no alias","A.N.","Doc","Dr. Nagata","Tyco","Mr. Johnson","Tycho Manager","Fred","Fred Johnson","Comms","Chief Medical Officer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Scopuli Report","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"The chief medical officer and second-in-command of the Rocinante, a tactical genius and expert in medicine.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain, leader"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Investigative partner"}],"recentEvents":"Discusses the potential for radiation shelters and essential personnel handling emergencies."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Amos Burton","aliases":["Amos","Amos 'Tango Down' Burton","Tango Down","Amo","A.B.","Mister Burton","Mr. Burton","Mechanical Genius","Chief","Chief Engineer"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Scopuli Report","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"The chief engineer of the Rocinante, known for his aggressive personality but also for his loyalty to Holden and the crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain, leader"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Alex Kamal","relationship":"Crewmate"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Investigative partner"}],"recentEvents":"Fends off people pushing in the crowd; confirms with Holden they will head towards their ship, the Rocinante."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid","Governor Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Strict and unyielding leader of Ceres under United Nations supervision, now overseeing the peaceful transition of governance.","relationships":[{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Detective partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Head detective"}],"recentEvents":"Declared the transition of governance from Earth to a provisional local government due to Mars' requests."},{"name":"Shirtless","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A steroid-pumped Belt rioter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered a woman and was incapacitated by Miller."},{"name":"The Woman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."},{"name":"Unnamed Security Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Eros Emergency","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A security officer dressed in fake police uniform, part of a corrupt group controlling the crowd.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","rela