ger","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A space station in the asteroid belt populated by miners and settlers","recentEvents":"Ceres experienced several riots and a curfew was imposed to maintain stability amid growing tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is caught in the conflict between Mars and Earth"},{"location":"Tycho","relationship":"Ceres residents begin to seek refuge on Tycho"}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros Station","aliases":["the playhouse","Eros","asteroid","eros"],"arc":"Eros","description":"An asteroid station where a secret corporate project is taking place.","recentEvents":"Mercenaries abandoned their posts for unknown reasons, allowing Miller and Holden to proceed unimpeded towards the port.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Eros has a connection to Ceres, a location where initial actions concerning the plot originated."}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymed