:"Miller uncovers that the security personnel on Eros are part of a prolonged, coordinated effort using stolen Ceres Station equipment, indicating a much larger and more complex conspiracy."},{"name":"Radiation Shelter Discoveries","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller discover that the radiation shelters are laced with gas and radiation, leading to the conclusion that the population may have been infected or poisoned."},{"name":"Escape from Eros","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Josephus Miller"],"summary":"Miller and Holden successfully navigate through Eros to their hideout but discover that Naomi, Alex, and Amos are missing."},{"name":"Miller and Holden's Dilemma","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller are now facing immediate danger as they attempt to navigate through the violence and reach Holden's ship, searching for essential medication."},{"name":"Miller and Holden's Escape from Eros","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller and Holden successfully navigate the chaos of Eros, following the withdrawing mercenaries in their attempt to escape the deteriorating situation."},{"name":"Holden and Miller Escape Eros","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller","Amos"],"summary":"Holden and Miller narrowly escape Eros's conflict by donning stolen armor and making a harrowing dash towards the Rocinante, with Amos arriving at critical moment to provide extraction and immediate safety."}],"summary":"Holden and Miller face extreme danger and hostility on Eros while attempting to rescue Naomi. Severely injured, they manage to escape and seek refuge on the Rocinante, where they are greeted by Amos."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":36,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback","N/A","Muss","Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss",