e OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."},{"name":"Unnamed Security Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Eros Emergency","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A security officer dressed in fake police uniform, part of a corrupt group controlling the crowd.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Recognized from previous arrest"}],"recentEvents":"Observed by Miller as part of the corrupt security force, recognized as previously arrested and wearing stolen equipment."},{"name":"Ko (Unnamed security guard)","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 13: The Hole","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Security guard working for the Protogen corporation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Was injured by Miller and killed when he could not be saved."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Current","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"High-ranking executive at Protogen who orchestrated the presentation on the discovery of the protomolecule on Phoebe.","relationships":[{"character":"Protogen Board Members","relationship":"Reports to"}],"recentEvents":"Gave a presentation touting the discovery of an extraterrestrial weapon on Phoebe by Protogen and urged immediate and decisive action to control and research the protomolecule."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"The fourth planet in the solar system, a major power involved in the conflict with the Belt.","recentEvents":"James Holden and the Canterbury raised concerns about the possibility of war between Mars and the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Belt","relationship":"Mars is in conflict with the Belt over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"A space station in the asteroid belt populated by miners and settlers","recentEvents":"Ceres experienced several riots and a curfew was imposed to maintain stability amid growing tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Ceres is caught in the conflict between Mars and Earth"},{"location":"Tycho","relationship":"Ceres residents begin to seek refuge on Tycho"}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros Station","aliases":["the playhouse","Eros","asteroid","eros","415 Eros"],"arc":"The Protomolecule Experiment","description":"A small asteroid and former space station where a significant experiment involving the protomolecule took place.","recentEvents":"Eros is referenced in discussions about Protogen's experiments and the subsequent chaos, implying that the company used the asteroid for testing and that something catastrophic occurred.","relationships":[{"location":"Phoebe","relationship":"Site of initial discovery of the protomolecule"},{"location":"Saturn","relationship":"Phoebe orbits Saturn, making it part of Saturn's system"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","arc":"Conflict","description":"A large moon of Jupiter, significant for its role in interplanetary trade and being a staging point for operations involving Ceres.","recentEvents":"Serves as the destination for the Black Cat freighter carrying stolen police equipment from Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]},{"name":"Tachi","arc":"The Donnager Event","description":"A salvaged MCRN gunboat now in Jim Holden's possession.","recentEvents":"Jim Holden and his crew use Tachi to escape the battle and seek refuge from the MCRN.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN","relationship":"Currently evading"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho Manufacturing and Engineering Concern"],"arc":"The Expansion","description":"A large orbital station circling a planet, serving as a hub for space travel and commerce.","recentEvents":"The crew is spending time on Tycho to rest and gather information before deciding their next steps.","relationships":[{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"The crew visits and repairs the ship docked at Tycho"}]},{"name":"Ship Rocinante","aliases":["Roci","Rocinante"],"arc":"Mao","description":"A warship now converted into a fugitive hunter vessel, carrying Captain Holden and Miller.","recentEvents":"The crew of the Rocinante return from Eros but face the aftermath of their violent actions, dealing with the psychological toll of their battles and recovery from their injuries.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Recently departed from mission site"},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"In vicinity of Earth near Eros station"}]},{"name":"Triton","arc":"Conflict","description":"A moon of Neptune with a deep astronomy lab occupied by OPA supporters","recentEvents":"Triton's astronomy lab was taken over and used to broadcast sensitive information about Mars, escalating tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Broadcasting details of Mars' military positions and activities"},{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Increased unrest on Ceres due to Triton's actions"}]},{"name":"Triton Astronomy Lab","arc":"Conflict","description":"A facility on Triton taken over by a band of OPA supporters for broadcasting","recentEvents":"Used to broadcast the locations of all Martian ships and high-definition images of Mars, causing further tension.","relationships":[{"location":"Triton","relationship":"Contained within Triton and a hot spot of conflict"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Causing significant information leaks about Mars' military positions"}]},{"name":"Tycho","arc":"Tycho","description":"A large facility established on the Moon's surface.","recentEvents":"Holden negotiates with Fred Johnson to work for him and is tasked with retrieving a man named Lionel Polanski from Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Eros is one of the many orbital stations serving the Tycho facility as part of Fred Johnson's operations"}]},{"name":"Phoebe","arc":"The Protomolecule Experiment","description":"A small, icy moon of Saturn in an extra-ecliptic orbit, where an alien artifact was discovered.","recentEvents":"Discussed as the origin site of the protomolecule, a weapon discovered by Protogen during a Martian-sponspored scientific survey.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn","relationship":"Orbits Saturn"},{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Source of the protomolecule tested on Eros"}]},{"name":"Saturn","arc":"The Protomolecule Experiment","description":"A gas giant in the outer solar system, home to Phoebe and its extra-ecliptic orbit.","recentEvents":"Saturn is mentioned as the orbit of Phoebe, the site where the protomolecule was discovered.","relationships":[{"location":"Phoebe","relationship":"Phoebe is one of Saturn's moons"},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Saturn is a part of the solar system"}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Radiation Shelter Discoveries","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller discover that the radiation shelters are laced with gas and radiation, leading to the conclusion that the population may have been infected or poisoned."},{"name":"Escape from Eros","status":"active","characters":["James Holden","Josephus Miller"],"summary":"Miller and Holden successfully navigate through Eros to their hideout but discover that Naomi, Alex, and Amos are missing."},{"name":"Miller and Holden's Dilemma","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller are now facing immediate danger as they attempt to navigate through the violence and reach Holden's ship, searching for essential medication."},{"name":"Miller and Holden's Escape from Eros","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller and Holden successfully navigate the chaos of Eros, following the withdrawing mercenaries in their attempt to escape the deteriorating situation."},{"name":"Holden and Miller Escape Eros","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller","Amos"],"summary":"Holden and Miller narrowly escape Eros's conflict by donning stolen armor and making a harrowing dash towards the Rocinante, with Amos arriving at critical moment to provide extraction and immediate safety."},{"name":"Personal Relationships on Rocinante","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden","Naomi"],"summary":"Miller advises Holden on his relationship with Naomi, suggesting he invest more effort into understanding and pursuing her."},{"name":"The Scopuli Mystery","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Amos","Naomi","Alex","Miller"],"summary":"The mystery of the Scopuli's destruction and the identity of the stealth ship involved is becoming clearer as the crew identifies a potential culprit near Eros."},{"name":"Protogen's Agenda","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Miller"],"summary":"Holden and Miller uncover Protogen's secretive and potentially dangerous experiments with the alien protomolecule, revealing the company's disregard for safety and ethical considerations."}],"summary":"The Rifter crew uncovers the origins of the protomolecule through corporate archives, revealing that Protogen, a research company, discovered the alien artifact on the moon Phoebe and has since been conducting dangerous experiments on it, including the recent disaster on Eros. The extent of the corporation's manipulation and ambition in pursuit of the protomolecule's power is becoming apparent."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"},{"index":39,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Juliette Andromeda Mao","aliases":["Julie Mao","Jules","Razorback","N/A","Muss","Captain","Mr. Jim","Jim Holden","Captain Shaddid","Jim","James Holden","Boss","Captain Holden","William Orlowski","Havelock","Billy Havelock","Wayne Havelock","Candace","Willis Havelock","Detective Muss","Krista Muss","Miller","Joseph Michael Miller","Julie","Detective","Earth Dog","Joseph Miller","the cop","Josephus Miller","Cop","James Miller","Joseph","old man","cerebral cop","cop","peace officer","Detective Miller","The man with the hat","Joseph Sematimba","partner","Juliette Mao","Cap&#39;n","none","Anderson Dawes","Joe","Cap","Holden","Cap'n","Joe Miller"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Requiem","currentLocation":"Naiad","description":"A seasoned detective with a personal vendetta against crime and corruption, former Martian Security Forces officer.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Investigating Holden's daughter Julie Mao's case"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Investigating disappearance of Holden's daughter"},{"character":"Amos Burton","relationship":"Colleague and crewmate"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Colleague and crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Showed James Holden recordings of Martian news reports depicting Earth ships attacking Martian ships, re