iller","relationship":"Colleague and crewmate"}],"recentEvents":"Ordered to rest after the destruction of the stealth ship."},{"name":"Becca Orlowski","aliases":["Rebecca","Orlowski"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: The Last Serenity","currentLocation":"Canterbury","description":"The communications officer aboard the Canterbury.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Communications Officer"},{"character":"William Orlowski","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Ava Tukunbo","relationship":"Navigator"},{"character":"Mark Paj","relationship":"Engineer"}],"recentEvents":"Becca sent out a message to the broken ship and informed Ceres about the unexpected detour."},{"name":"Javier Liu","aliases":["Javier"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"A structural engineer from Tycho, now with his grandchildren running his bar the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Cassio Ramachandra","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Talking with members of the vice and exploitation team in his bar."},{"name":"Kate Liu","aliases":["Kate"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Fourth generation owner of the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge.","relationships":[{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"grandfather"}],"recentEvents":"Serving drinks to Miller and Havelock."},{"name":"Cassio Ramachandra","aliases":["Ramachandra"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 4","currentLocation":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","description":"Star Helix Security's top officer, working for Amunet, known for his sharp mind and a penchant for using Miller's alias.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"fellow Star Helix Security agent, co-worker"},{"character":"Yevgeny Cobb","relationship":"fellow homicide officer"},{"character":"Javier Liu","relationship":"acquaintance"}],"recentEvents":"Present in the Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge when the alert came in."},{"name":"Pramod Rao","aliases":["Shaddid","Governor Shaddid"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Strict and unyielding leader of Ceres under United Nations supervision, now overseeing the peaceful transition of governance.","relationships":[{"character":"Muss","relationship":"Detective partner"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Head detective"}],"recentEvents":"Declared the transition of governance from Earth to a provisional local government due to Mars' requests."},{"name":"Shirtless","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A steroid-pumped Belt rioter.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered a woman and was incapacitated by Miller."},{"name":"The Woman","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Victim of the Belt riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Murdered by Shirtless during the riot."},{"name":"The OPA Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Station dock","description":"A supporter of the Outer Planets Alliance involved in the station riot.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Challenged Miller's authority during the riot but backed down."},{"name":"Julian","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Home","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A friend of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Not mentioned in recent events."},{"name":"Theresa Yao","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter title where they last appeared","currentLocation":"Donnager","description":"Captain of the MCRN Donnager, the battleship that is to pick up Holden's crew.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"target of investigation"}],"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."},{"name":"Unnamed Security Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Eros Emergency","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A security officer dressed in fake police uniform, part of a corrupt group controlling the crowd.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Recognized from previous arrest"}],"recentEvents":"Observed by Miller as part of the corrupt security force, recognized as previously arrested and wearing stolen equipment."},{"name":"Ko (Unnamed security guard)","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 13: The Hole","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Security guard working for the Protogen corporation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Was injured by Miller and killed when he could not be saved."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Current","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"High-ranking executive at Protogen who orchestrated the presentation on the discovery of the protomolecule on Phoebe.","relationships":[{"character":"Protogen Board Members","relationship":"Reports to"}],"recentEvents":"Gave a presentation touting the discovery of an extraterrestrial weapon on Phoebe by Protogen and urged immediate and decisive action to control and research the protomolecule."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Di