sts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.",