:"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Opponent, Debater"}],"recentEvents":"Gave a detailed pitch to James Holden and his team about the necessity and potential of the Protogen project, including altering scientists to be high-functioning sociopaths."},{"name":"Chrisjen Avasarala","importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A senior Martian political leader involved in high-stakes negotiations and military strategy.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Works with Holden on political and military issues"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Works with Miller on investigations"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Had personal conflicts but worked together"}],"recentEvents":"Avasarala was likely instrumental in the Martian navy's decision to destroy the Phoebe science station around Saturn.","aliases":["Avasarala","CJ"]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":[],"importance":"government","status":"active","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Mars","description":"The Mars government is the main political entity in charge of Mars and is involved in decisions about the Belt and its resources.","relationships":[{"character":"Chrisjen Avasarala","relationship":"Avasarala represents Mars government interests"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Holden allies with Mars government during critical situations"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Miller works with Mars government to solve Belt problems"}],"recentEvents":"Mars government took decisive action by destroying the Phoebe science station around Saturn."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Talbot Leeds","description":"A young demolitions crew member on the Talbot Leeds.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Works with Miller during demolition mission"}],"recentEvents":"Diogo informed Miller abou