"recentEvents":"Communicated with the crew of Knight regarding course and advised against further general broadcasts."},{"name":"Ariadne Mao","aliases":["Mama Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The mother of Julie Mao and wife of Jules-Pierre Mao, involved in family business and estranged family relations.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Jules-Pierre Mao","relationship":"Husband"}],"recentEvents":"Sent a message to Julie warning her about the safety of the Belt."},{"name":"Jules-Pierre Mao","aliases":["JP Mao"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter 7: The Abyss","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"CEO of the Mao-Kwikowski Mercantile and father of Julie Mao, involved in consolidating his business properties.","relationships":[{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Daughter"},{"character":"Ariadne Mao","relationship":"Wife"}],"recentEvents":"Going through a consolidation phase and considering selling the Razorback."},{"name":"Vincent Havelock","aliases":[],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"A younger detective with a keen interest in justice and a strong sense of morality.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Partner"}],"recentEvents":"Waited for Miller at the station, expressed concern for his well-being."},{"name":"Unidentified OPA Leader","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Ain't No Justice","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A pock-faced man in a bar who spoke confidently about OPA's operations.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Miller","relationship":"Interacted with"}],"recentEvents":"Discussed OPA's political stance with Miller, warned him not to return to the bar."},{"name":"Lopez","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A mariner with the Rocinante, primarily a medic and a pilot.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Captain and crew member"}],"recentEvents":"Lopez is not mentioned in this chapter."},{"name":"A marine officer","importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Tug of War","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A naval intelligence officer on the Donnager who questioned James Holden.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Interviewed subject"}],"recentEvents":"The officer questioned Holden and left his quarters during the battle."},{"name":"Dawes","aliases":["Agent Dawes"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Chapter: Earth Is Pulling Out","currentLocation":"Ceres Station","description":"Station official often in discussions with Shaddid about station affairs and stability.","relationships":[{"character":"Shaddid","relationship":"Station official"},{"character":"Miller","relationship":"Contacts in station affairs"}],"recentEvents":"Was present in Shaddid's office for the announcement of Miller's firing and the new state of affairs."},{"name":"Hasini","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Drunk","currentLocation":"Ceres","description":"Owner of a bar named Blue Frog, helpful and concerned about the well-being of regular patrons like Miller.","relationships":[{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"Bar regular and patron"}],"recentEvents":"Helped a drunk and troubled Miller by taking him home in an electric cart."},{"name":"Lionel Polanski","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"","currentLocation":"Eros","description":"An imaginary owner of the Scopuli who checks into a flophouse.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Is a code name for an individual requiring covert assistance."},{"name":"Chang Chen Sematimba","aliases":["Chang","Semati"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Auburn and Beyond","currentLocation":"Bucharest","description":"Head of Bucharest security, a longtime friend and colleague of Miller's.","relationships":[{"character":"Joseph Michael Miller","relationship":"Friend and colleague"}],"recentEvents":"Called to the scene where Miller found Juliette Mao's body."},{"name":"Unnamed Security Man","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Eros Emergency","currentLocation":"Eros Station","description":"A security officer dressed in fake police uniform, part of a corrupt group controlling the crowd.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Recognized from previous arrest"}],"recentEvents":"Observed by Miller as part of the corrupt security force, recognized as previously arrested and wearing stolen equipment."},{"name":"Ko (Unnamed security guard)","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"dead","lastSeen":"Chapter 13: The Hole","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"Security guard working for the Protogen corporation.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"Was injured by Miller and killed when he could not be saved."},{"name":"Mr. Dresden","aliases":["Dresden"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Infiltration","currentLocation":"Unnamed Eros station","description":"Administrator of the captured Eros station owned by the corporation Protogen.","relationships":[{"character":"Colonel Johnson","relationship":"Administrator of the facility Johnson and OPA forces attacked"},{"character":"James Miller","relationship":"In charge of capturing the mission's goal"}],"recentEvents":"Conversed with Colonel Johnson about terms of capitulation, offering resources in exchange for freedom to leave."},{"name":"Alexander Dresden","aliases":["Aleks","Dr. Dresden"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Unknown","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A scientist and leader of the Protogen project, who has adopted ethically questionable methods for the sake of scientific progress.","relationships":[{"character":"James Holden","relationship":"Opponent, Negotiator"},{"character":"Naomi Nagata","relationship":"Opponent, Debater"}],"recentEvents":"Gave a detailed pitch to James Holden and his team about the necessity and potential of the Protogen project, including altering scientists to be high-functioning sociopaths."},{"name":"Chrisjen Avasarala","importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A senior Martian political leader involved in high-stakes negotiations and military strategy.","relationships":[{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Works with Holden on political and military issues"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Works with Miller on investigations"},{"character":"Julie Mao","relationship":"Had personal conflicts but worked together"}],"recentEvents":"Avasarala was likely instrumental in the Martian navy's decision to destroy the Phoebe science station around Saturn.","aliases":["Avasarala","CJ"]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":[],"importance":"government","status":"active","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Mars","description":"The Mars government is the main political entity in charge of Mars and is involved in decisions about the Belt and its resources.","relationships":[{"character":"Chrisjen Avasarala","relationship":"Avasarala represents Mars government interests"},{"character":"Jim Holden","relationship":"Holden allies with Mars government during critical situations"},{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Miller works with Mars government to solve Belt problems"}],"recentEvents":"Mars government took decisive action by destroying the Phoebe science station around Saturn."},{"name":"Diogo","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Calabar Crisis","currentLocation":"Talbot Leeds","description":"A young demolitions crew member on the Talbot Leeds.","relationships":[{"character":"Josephus Miller","relationship":"Works with Miller during demolition mission"}],"recentEvents":"Diogo informed Miller about Mars' destruction of the Phoebe science station and speculated on Mars forming an alliance with OPA."}],"locations":[{"name":"The Scopuli","aliases":["Scopuli"],"arc":"Piracy","description":"A ship that has been attacked and abandoned, located in the belt between planets.","recentEvents":"Jim and Amos investigate the ship and discover a fake distress beacon that led to the discovery of the derelict ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Investigation crew arrives to the site of the distress call from Scopuli"}]},{"name":"Canterbury","aliases":["The Canterbury","Canter"],"arc":"War","description":"A commercial transport ship destroyed in a surprise attack.","recentEvents":"A group of survivors from the destroyed Canterbury have been rescued and are now being transported to safety, but they face new dangers aboard the ship.","relationships":[{"location":"Hangar Bay","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury where the survivors are hiding and trying to escape"}]},{"name":"CA-2216862","arc":"Emergency and Rescue","description":"A charted non-Belt asteroid near which the distressed Scopuli is located.","recentEvents":"The Scopuli is found in the vicinity of this asteroid in distress.","relationships":[{"location":"Scopuli","relationship":"Scopuli is located near it"}]},{"name":"Knight","aliases":["ship"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A ship belonging to the crew whose fate is entwined with the mysterious protomolecule and its effects.","recentEvents":"Crew received a message from Colonel Johnson, an influential figure in the Outer Planets Alliance, warning them against coercion and offering assistance if they need it.","relationships":[{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"Knight is being pursued by this Martian battlecruiser"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"Colonel Johnson offers support from this organization"}]},{"name":"Blue Frog Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"An entertainment venue on Ceres where local security officers gather.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock initially struggle with their relationship there; Miller later turns the conversation around with help from the bar staff and his colleagues.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Distinguished Hyacinth Lounge","arc":"Conflict","description":"A bar frequented by Ceres security personnel, including Star Helix Security.","recentEvents":"Miller and Havelock continue their conversation here, addressing Havelock's concerns and turning it into a more positive interaction.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Part of"}]},{"name":"Martian Congressional Republic","arc":"Conflict","description":"The government and military of Mars.","recentEvents":"The stealth ship involved in the destruction of the Canterbury appears to be equipped with technology that bears the serial number of the Martian navy.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"The ship's destruction by the stealth ship raised suspicions about involvement with Mars military technology"}]},{"name":"Cantnery Belt","arc":"Conflict","description":"A region in space surrounding Saturn, known for having numerous asteroids and other space debris.","recentEvents":"Six unidentified dark ships are intercepted on a course that will bring them to the Knight near the edge of the Belt.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"The unidentified ships are approaching Knight's location in the Belt."}]},{"name":"Mars","aliases":["Red Planet"],"arc":"The Deep","description":"The neighboring planet to Earth, home to a significant human population and in conflict with Earth.","recentEvents":"Martian night sky lit up by missiles and dying ships as Earth ships attack in orbit.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Engaged in interplanetary conflict with Earth over hidden naval forces"}]},{"name":"Luna","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"Earth's moon, a key player in the Belt-Mars conflict, and home to the Mao-Kwikowski family's headquarters.","recentEvents":"Julie Mao's mother, Ariadne Mao, sends a message from Luna to Julie about the fate of the Razorback.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Luna is in close association with Earth, playing a role in the Belt-Mars conflicts."},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Luna has significant ties and conflicts with Mars over resources and political power."}]},{"name":"Razorback","arc":"Politics and Conflict","description":"A personal boat of Julie Mao, significant due to her father's contemplation of selling it.","recentEvents":"The fate of the Razorback is in question as Julie's parents consider selling it.","relationships":[{"location":"Julie Mao","relationship":"The Razorback is closely associated with Julie Mao, a personal possession with sentimental and logistical value for her."}]},{"name":"Outer Planets Alliance","aliases":["OPA"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A political body representing the interests of inhabitants of the outer planets, potentially aligned against Mars.","recentEvents":"Colonel Johnson of the OPA reaches out to the Knight crew, urging caution and informing them of potential threats to their freedom.","relationships":[{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Attempted to support the Knight crew against potential coercion"},{"location":"Donnager","relationship":"OPA warns against Martian influence"}]},{"name":"Ceres Station","aliases":["Ceres","Cererean"],"arc":"Interplanetary Politics","description":"A space station and the core location of Belt politics, situated in the main asteroid belt.","recentEvents":"Fred negotiates a peace conference with Earth and Mars representatives on Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Earth","relationship":"A key interplanetary power in negotiations with Ceres and Mars"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"A key interplanetary power in negotiations with Ceres and Earth"}]},{"name":"SS Donnager","aliases":["MCRN Donnager","Martian battlecruiser","Donnager"],"arc":"Attack on Donnager","description":"A powerful Martian battlecruiser that threatens the crew's freedom.","recentEvents":"The Donnager encounters a group of unidentified ships and engages in a brutal battle with point defense systems and gauss turrets active. The ship is hit by a torpedo, and internal damage is caused.","relationships":[{"location":"Unknown ships","relationship":"Engaged in battle against"},{"location":"Knight","relationship":"Pursuing the Knight ship"},{"location":"Outer Planets Alliance","relationship":"The OPA warns about the influence of this battlecruiser"}]},{"name":"Eros Station","aliases":["the playhouse","Eros","asteroid","eros","415 Eros","Eros asteroid","space station"],"arc":"Encounter","description":"A small asteroid mining site transformed by the protomolecule and home to Juliette Andromeda Mao","recentEvents":"Juliette Mao, now transformed by the protomolecule, is persuaded by Miller to divert Eros away from Earth to Venus.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Former mining site and the source of Star Helix Security's contract to find Juliette Mao"},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"The intended destination that Eros is diverted away from"},{"location":"Venus","relationship":"New destination towards which Eros is being steered"}]},{"name":"Hangar Bay","arc":"War","description":"A part of the Canterbury where spacecraft can be stored and launched.","recentEvents":"Survivors attempt to escape in a commandeered corvette, while facing enemy boarders.","relationships":[{"location":"Canterbury","relationship":"Part of the Canterbury"}]},{"name":"Ganymede","arc":"Conflict","description":"A large moon of Jupiter, significant for its role in interplanetary trade and being a staging point for operations involving Ceres.","recentEvents":"Serves as the destination for the Black Cat freighter carrying stolen police equipment from Ceres.","relationships":[{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"The Black Cat freighter transported stolen police equipment and personnel to Ganymede from Ceres."}]},{"name":"Tachi","arc":"The Donnager Event","description":"A salvaged MCRN gunboat now in Jim Holden's possession.","recentEvents":"Jim Holden and his crew use Tachi to escape the battle and seek refuge from the MCRN.","relationships":[{"location":"MCRN","relationship":"Currently evading"}]},{"name":"Tycho Station","aliases":["Tycho Manufacturing and Engineering Concern","Tycho"],"arc":"The Asteroid Threat","description":"A station in the Tycho system where the OPA freighters remain active on the surface of Eros.","recentEvents":"The Roci team uses freighter control codes provided by Miller to reactivate transponders on Tycho Station’s surface and guide the tracking of Eros.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"The freighters have been moored to Eros to assist in its tracking."},{"location":"Roci","relationship":"Tycho Station serves as a hub for the tracking of Eros via reactivated freighter transponders."}]},{"name":"Ship Rocinante","aliases":["Roci","Rocinante"],"arc":"Eros","description":"The ship crewed by the main characters, responsible for pivotal actions in the solar system events.","recentEvents":"The crew watches the transformation of Eros via broadcast while en route to Tycho.","relationships":[{"location":"Venus","relationship":"Rocinante observes the events from a distance as they unfold on and around Venus."}]},{"name":"Triton","arc":"Conflict","description":"A moon of Neptune with a deep astronomy lab occupied by OPA supporters","recentEvents":"Triton's astronomy lab was taken over and used to broadcast sensitive information about Mars, escalating tensions.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Broadcasting details of Mars' military positions and activities"},{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Increased unrest on Ceres due to Triton's actions"}]},{"name":"Triton Astronomy Lab","arc":"Conflict","description":"A facility on Triton taken over by a band of OPA supporters for broadcasting","recentEvents":"Used to broadcast the locations of all Martian ships and high-definition images of Mars, causing further tension.","relationships":[{"location":"Triton","relationship":"Contained within Triton and a hot spot of conflict"},{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Causing significant information leaks about Mars' military positions"}]},{"name":"Phoebe","arc":"Protogen's Ambition","description":"A moon of Saturn, destroyed by the Martian government due to potential contamination.","recentEvents":"The Martian navy destroyed Phoebe to prevent further contamination by the protomolecular material.","relationships":[{"location":"Saturn","relationship":"Phoebe was one of Saturn's moons, destroyed to contain a potential protomolecular threat."}]},{"name":"Saturn","arc":"The Protomolecule Experiment","description":"A gas giant in the outer solar system, home to Phoebe and its extra-ecliptic orbit.","recentEvents":"Saturn is mentioned as the orbit of Phoebe, the site where the protomolecule was discovered.","relationships":[{"location":"Phoebe","relationship":"Phoebe is one of Saturn's moons"},{"location":"Earth","relationship":"Saturn is a part of the solar system"}]},{"name":"Earth","aliases":["Earth-Mars Coalition Navy"],"arc":"The Deep","description":"The home planet of humanity, involved in a conflict with Mars over hidden naval forces.","recentEvents":"Earth ships destroyed Martian radar station and engaged in battle with Martian counterparts.","relationships":[{"location":"Mars","relationship":"Engaged in interplanetary conflict with Earth over hidden naval forces"}]},{"name":"Guy Molinari","aliases":["Cargo ship"],"arc":"Rescue","description":"A cargo ship full of OPA soldiers about to embark on a mission to Thoth Station","recentEvents":"Arrived at Thoth Station to begin the assault.","relationships":[{"location":"Thoth Station","relationship":"Mission target"}]},{"name":"Thoth Station","arc":"Rescue","description":"A station collecting data from Eros and believed to be harboring dangerous secrets.","recentEvents":"Targeted by an assault force comprised of the Rocinante and the Guy Molinari, aiming to uncover truths from the station’s crew and data.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Data source"},{"location":"Anderson Station","relationship":"Former antagonist controlled by Fred Johnson"},{"location":"Ceres","relationship":"Previous setting where key characters met"}]},{"name":"Station (nearby Station)","aliases":["Nearby Station","Neighboring Space Station"],"arc":"Conflict","description":"An orbiting station near which the Rocinante fought its battle, likely providing assistance.","recentEvents":"The station coordinated the rescue of the crew from the damaged Rocinante.","relationships":[{"location":"Rocinante","relationship":"Provides emergency assistance and docking services to a damaged ship."}]},{"name":"Protogen","arc":"The Protomolecule's Arrival","description":"A private company conducting research on the protomolecule in the Belt.","recentEvents":"Scientists and technicians have been modified into high-functioning sociopaths to continue experiments at the cost of human lives, and a security team oversees the operations.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Protogen's research and experiments on the protomolecule take place on Eros."}]},{"name":"Nauvoo","arc":"Conflict - Defending Humanity","description":"A massive ship under construction that can potentially move large stations and objects.","recentEvents":"Fred considers using the Nauvoo to drive Eros into the sun to ensure the protomolecule's destruction.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Proposed to be impacted by the Nauvoo moving it into the sun"}]},{"name":"United Nations Military","aliases":["UN Forces","UN Navy"],"arc":"The Protomolecule","description":"A collective term for the military and naval forces established and controlled by the United Nations, responsible for maintaining order and security across the solar system.","recentEvents":"In response to the conflict near Eros, the UN military mobilizes a significant force, indicating the high stakes involved in the situation.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"The UN military is sending ships to establish control over Eros and nearby areas."}]},{"name":"Venus","arc":"Eros","description":"The second planet of the solar system that becomes the site of a significant event.","recentEvents":"Eros splits and disperses in Venus's atmosphere, spreading the protomolecule over the planet.","relationships":[{"location":"Eros","relationship":"Eros transforms and enters into orbit around Venus before dispersing."}]}],"arcs":[{"name":"Chasing Eros","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Alex","Fred","McBride"],"summary":"Holden and the crew develop a new plan to target Eros using OPA freighters' transponders and relay communications, setting course for a decisive confrontation."},{"name":"The Protomolecule's Origins","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Holden"],"summary":"Miller realizes that the protomolecule is utilizing the neural structures and languages of the dead population of Eros, possibly including Juliette Mao."},{"name":"Miller's Mission on Eros","status":"active","characters":["Miller"],"summary":"Miller now seeks to locate and communicate with Juliette Mao within the protomolecule, marking a critical pivot in his mission."},{"name":"Miller's Mission","status":"active","characters":["Miller","Julie"],"summary":"Miller embarks on a mission to find Julie and potentially talk to the entity controlling Eros, buying time through Holden's strategic maneuvering."},{"name":"The Protomolecule","status":"active","characters":["Julie","Miller"],"summary":"Julie has taken control over the station's course, and Miller is in the process of being transformed by the protomolecule alongside Julie."},{"name":"Protomolecule Puzzle","status":"active","characters":["Holden","Naomi","Amos","Alex"],"summary":"Now that Eros is neutralized, new questions arise about the origins and future implications of the protomolecule, hinting at further mysteries to be unraveled."},{"name":"Miller's Sacrifice and Legacy","status":"active","characters":["Josephus Aloisus Miller","James Holden","Josephus Foss"],"summary":"Miller's death becomes a focal point for political maneuvering, with Fred attempting to leverage his sacrifice as a symbol for Belt solidarity and Holden pushing back to preserve Miller's individuality."},{"name":"Negotiating the Peace","status":"active","characters":["Josephus Foss","James Holden","various political representatives"],"summary":"Fred prepares to deliver a speech aimed at using Miller's sacrifice as a rallying cry for peace and Belt representation, while Holden insists on the importance of preserving Miller's identity."}],"summary":"Fred, now a significant political figure, is orchestrating a peace conference on Ceres to discuss the future of Earth, Mars, and the Belt. Holden visits Fred to discuss amnesty for Belters and the memory of Miller, whose sacrifice is being used as a political tool."},"model":"qwen2.5:14b","appVersion":"dev"}],"bookMeta":{"chapters":[{"id":"titlepage","title":"Part 1","order":0,"bookIndex":0,"bookTitle":"Part 1"},{"id":"copyright","title":"Part 2","order":1,"bookIndex":1,"bookTitle":"Part 2"},{"id":"contents","title":"Part 3","order":2,"bookIndex":2,"bookTitle":"Part 3"},{"id":"section1","title":"Part 4","order":3,"bookIndex":3,"bookTitle":"Part 4"},{"id":"section3","title":"Prologue: Julie","order":4,"bookIndex":3,"bookTitle":"Part 4"},{"id":"section4","title":"Chapter One: Holden","order":5,"bookIndex":3,"bookTitle":"Part 4"},{"id":"section5","title":"Chapter Two: Miller","order":6,"bookIndex":3,"bookTitle":"Part 4"},